<br>
<p align="left"><b>LITERATURE SURVEY</b></p>
<p><b>2.1 Introduction</b><br>
An AI Code Generator Chatbot is an intelligent tool that helps developers write code more efficiently. This survey explains the current methods used by developers for coding assistance and highlights the drawbacks in existing systems.</p>

<p><b>2.2 Existing System</b><br>
Currently, developers manually write code, searching through documentation, forums, or using standard IDE auto-completion like IntelliSense. These approaches often require significant context switching between the integrated development environment, documentation, and web searches, which continuously interrupts the workflow.</p>

<p><b>2.3 Current Methods / Tools</b><br>
Developers heavily rely on manual searching across multiple websites, documentation portals, and standard code editors to piece together basic syntax, find debugging solutions, or learn best practices.</p>

<p><b>2.4 Limitations</b><br>
The existing system has several major drawbacks. Manual searching across multiple websites is incredibly time-consuming. Basic search engines do not possess conversational memory, meaning they do not remember previous questions. Standard tools lack context and do not understand the specific intention or logic of what the developer is trying to build. Furthermore, there is a high learning curve, as beginners find it particularly hard to piece together fragmented solutions found online.</p>

<p><b>2.5 Summary</b><br>
The literature survey clearly shows that the current methods of writing and searching for code are slow and lack context. There is a strong need for an interactive system with conversational memory that instantly provides contextual code solutions.</p>

<br>
<p align="left"><b>PROBLEM STATEMENT</b></p>
<p>Writing code from scratch is often a time-consuming and error-prone process. Developers spend a massive amount of time searching the internet for basic syntax, debugging errors, or best practices. Context-switching between an IDE, documentation, and a web search heavily interrupts the development workflow. Additionally, beginners frequently struggle to convert their logical ideas into actual programming code.</p>
<p>Therefore, there is a prominent need for a system that:</p>
<ul>
<li>Eliminates massive manual searching</li>
<li>Provides complete conversational memory</li>
<li>Instantly converts logical ideas into functioning code</li>
<li>Supports faster delivery and code execution</li>
<li>Prevents continuous context-switching</li>
</ul>

<br>
<p align="left"><b>PROPOSED SOLUTION</b></p>
<p><b>4.1 Introduction</b><br>
The proposed system is CodeGen, a smart chatbot that instantly generates code exactly when requested. It provides a reliable solution by delivering direct, final code instead of returning a list of website links. It focuses purely on contextual generation, automated processing, and smooth collaboration between the user and AI.</p>

<p><b>4.2 System Architecture</b><br>
The system architecture consists of a web frontend for the chat interface, an Express.js backend server, a local SQLite database, and an external AI engine.<br>
The user sends a request through the web frontend. The Express backend receives it, saves the context in the SQLite database, and forwards the prompt to an external AI Engine (OpenRouter / NVIDIA NIM). The AI intelligently generates the code, sends it back to the server, and it is cleanly formatted and displayed on the UI. The solution is securely hosted using Firebase for high scalability.</p>

<p><b>4.3 Working Process</b><br>
The working process involves several structured stages:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>User Input:</b> The user types a request, speaks into the microphone, or uploads a file representing their problem.</li>
<li><b>Context Retrieval:</b> The backend fetches past messages from the SQLite database to retrieve and understand the conversation history.</li>
<li><b>API Processing:</b> The backend packages the user prompt alongside the history and sends it securely to the AI Engine API.</li>
<li><b>Code Generation:</b> The AI processes the natural language instruction and generates the requested programming code.</li>
<li><b>Response Delivery:</b> The backend receives the AI response, saves it to the database for future memory contexts, and forwards it to the frontend.</li>
<li><b>Code Display:</b> The UI formats the code block with syntax highlighting for the user to easily copy, paste, and utilize.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>4.4 Features</b><br>
The CodeGen chatbot provides natural language code generation, instantly converting plain English requests into fully functional code. It offers wide multilingual support for programming languages like Python, Java, C++, and JavaScript. Conversational memory ensures the system deeply remembers the context of previous questions within the exact same chat session. The speech-to-text input smoothly allows users to dictate their problems via microphone, and the file analysis feature actively enables users to upload code files for the AI to debug or explain. Along with this, session management allows users to browse or delete past histories, while proper syntax highlighting neatly displays generated code.</p>

<p><b>4.5 Advantages</b><br>
The system reliably boosts productivity by generating complete boilerplate structures in seconds. It is highly beginner-friendly, and helps students grasp syntax and logic quickly. The application is cost-effective as it utilizes hosting on a free tier using Firebase alongside a lightweight backend. It is extremely versatile, dynamically assisting in writing new code, debugging existing code, or simplifying complex concepts. In addition, its web-based interface is fully accessible and demands no heavy local software installation.</p>

<p><b>4.6 Applications</b><br>
CodeGen is highly applicable in software developer spaces for rapid prototyping and rendering repetitive boilerplate code. In modern education and e-learning, it functions as a highly intelligent tutor for students learning computer programming. It is also exceptionally effective for code debugging to promptly discover syntax errors or logic flaws. Furthermore, it aids heavily in code refactoring by updating old code to modern standards or accurately translating it between differing languages.</p>

<p><b>4.7 Future Enhancements</b><br>
Exciting future enhancements involve the thorough integration of an IDE plugin, expanding the chatbot inherently into a VS Code extension for direct in-editor developer assistance. Building a quick one-click execution sandbox will reliably allow users to run generated code strictly directly in the browser UI. Engaging collaborative coding features will allow multiple independent users to seamlessly connect to the same session and prompt the AI engine together. Finally, integrating scaled offline local AI models will strategically eliminate long-term reliance on external internet APIs.</p>

<br>
<p align="left"><b>CONCLUSION</b></p>
<p>The AI Code Generator Chatbot is a powerful tool perfectly designed to deeply modernize software development. By utilizing advanced large language models alongside a highly user-friendly interface, it successfully handles the major ongoing problem of time-consuming manual coding and intensive error debugging. It reliably bridges the heavy gap between pure natural language logic and structured programming syntax. As Artificial Intelligence continuously evolves across the digital world, capable tools like this will become an essential, standard, and permanent part of every software developer's daily workflow.</p>
